msg: Fix references and dependencies.
Fix links.
Fix "@since <version>" lines.
Make escape sequences appear literally in explanation of MathJax.
Typo.

Make codebase Java 5 compatible.

The public API is comprised of 1 enum (with factory methods) and 2 interfaces.
The "internal" classes would not gain tremendously from more recent programming constructs (cf. changes in this commit).
Additional RNG implementations would be mostly low-level code (e.g. bit manipulation) also unlikely to be dependent on a modern JDK.

If and when considered, higher level utilities (e.g. "Stream"-based) could be implemented in another module, with more stringent requirements.
Forgotten uses of "diamond" operator (requires Java 7).

Bumped JDK dependency to Java 6 (due to "Arrays.copyOf").

Unlikely to loose many potential users w.r.t. Java 5.

JMH benchmarking enabled in "pom.xml".

Thanks to Artem Barger.

Benchmarking code example.

Thanks to Artem Barger.
Committed with some modifications.
Javadoc.
Cleanup.

JMH benchmarks.

Thanks to Artem Barger.
Cleanup.
Name of JHM result file.
Merge branch 'master' of https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf/commons-rng
CheckStyle.

Skip Mac related files.

Thanks to Artem Barger.

Correct JIRA numeric identifier.

Thanks to Artem Barger.
Depend on latest "commons-parent".
Doc cleanup.
Monte-Carlo integration as a usage example.
Javadoc.
Code moved to "src/userguide".

Customize RAT reporting.

Exclude automatically generated files (reports from external tools).
Update list of contributors.
User guide (usage overview).
User guide (library layout).
Small fixes (userguide).
Web site logo.

Useguide.

Fixed wrong link.
Set OSGi parameters defined in the parent POM.
Typos (userguide).

Userguide.

Update stress tests report.

  RNG-21

Manual revert.

As discussed on the ML, commit fd22dc61fd0ea75563ed893ad4857595de58a5dc
broke the generated "apidocs" (containing notes about user API and about
classes which contributors might need to touch).

There is no gain in hiding this one in particular, where others are also
"internal" but cannot be hidden in that way (short of putting them all
in the same package).
Moreover, it is possible that some usage might require access to the
"internal" classes.  In any case, classes within the "internal" package
are subject to change without notice, and application developers who want
to fiddle with them have been warned.

RNG-60: Use random seeds (unit test).

By using random seeds, it is expected that the unit tests will fail
with some probability; Junit is thus configured to rerun such a test,
marking it as "flaky" when it succeeds within the allotted number of
retries), and letting the build pass.

The parent POM uses maven-javadoc-plugin version 3. This changed the
<additionalparam> tag to <additionalOptions>.

Removed spurious assert statement from ProvidersCommonParametricTest.

The assertion that the intSeed is not equal to the original seed will
invoke Integer.equals(Object). I think the intention is to test the type
of the seed is correct, not the value.

Ensure full test coverage of MultiplyWithCarry256.

This removes the randomness from test coverage due to using random
seeds. Sometimes the conditional to set the carry using the absolute of
the first seed value was never hit.

are required.

msg:
RNG-70: Removed unnecessary constructors.

Tidy javadoc warning about zero seeds.
RNG-70: Fix javadoc and track changes.

Merge pull request #20 from aherbert/feature-RNG-70

RNG-70: Add new XoShiRo generators
Update JMH benchmarks for the XorShiRo generators.
Disable redundant JMH benchmarks and mark as deprecated.
Update JMH javadocs with notes on how to add new generators.
Removed redundant JMH benchmarks from examples.
Comment empty method in ThreadLocalPerformance benchmark.
Add a profile to build a shaded jar to run the JMH benchmarks.
InverseTransformParetoSampler: Pre-compute 1 / shape.

Updated the examples-stress application.

Auto detect the number of available processors.

Move utility methods used across commands to utils class.

Added OutputCommand to output raw data from an RNG.

Added BridgeTestCommand to replace the BridgeTester.

Added EndiannessCommand to show the native byte order.

Removed the obsolete testendianness.c program.

Updated the endianness example documentation.

msg:
Merge pull request #34 from aherbert/rng-utils

Updated examples stress command line application
Add the RandomSource name to the stress test result file

Renamed default stress test result prefix to test_.

Avoids name clash with the stress_test.md file.

Update examples-stress to Java 1.8.

Add stop file functionality to the stress command allowing ordered
shutdown.
RNG-92: LargeMeanPoissonSampler requires mean >= 1.
RNG-93: SmallMeanPoissonSampler requires probability p0 to be positive.
Fix build on Java 1.6 for LargeMeanPoissonSamplerTest
Fix typo.
Removed spurious Javadoc comment in the test.

RNG-91: Added a KempSmallMeanPoissonSampler

Add a benchmark to the JMH examples of various methods to compute a Poisson sample.

Corrected reference for the SmallMeanPoissonSampler.

The previously linked web page is no longer available.
Update pom.xml

Merge pull request #42 from AbhishekSinghDhadwal/master

Update contributors section of pom.xml
Added trial offset to the stress test application.
Update NOTICE file for 2019.
Do not close stdout when finished writing to it.
Remove final from method arguments (for consistency).
Added a results command to the stress test application.
Removed old stress test results

Ignore generated JMH files in checkstyle.
Updated description to match the module.
Fixed typo and updated deprecated generator.
Fixing sonar code issues and updated deprecated generator.
Merge branch 'feature-RNG-91'

Close #40

Fix bad braces.

- Simplify/rearrange boolean logic
- Use equals() to compare objects
Add pmd:check to travis

Merge pull request #45 from aherbert/fix-pmd

Fix code to pass pmd:check
Add defaultGoal to pom to match Travis checks.
Make utility classes final.

RNG-96: Fix parameter interpretation in the AhrensDieterMarsagliaTsangGammaSampler.

This modifies the algorithm so that alpha is interpreted as a 'shape'
parameter and theta is a 'scale' parameter. This effectively reverses
the function of the parameters (alpha => theta and theta => alpha). The
algorithm parameter names match those defined on MathWorld and
Wikipedia. The sampler output matches the reference definition in the
tests when the same parameters for shape and scale are used.
RNG-96: Updated the example distribution plots for the user guide.

Merge pull request #39 from aherbert/fix-RNG-96

RNG-96: Fix parameter interpretation in the AhrensDieterMarsagliaTsangGammaSampler

RNG-101: Add MarsagliaTsangWang discrete probability sampler.

This adds support for a generic distribution defined by an array of
probabilities and also a Poisson and Binomial distribution.

msg: RNG-101: Added MarsagliaTsangWang Poisson Sampler to the test list.
RNG-101: Added MarsagliaTsangWang samplers to the JMH benchmark.

RNG-101: Updated implementation to use factory methods for construction.

The methods can choose a concrete implementation that has optimal
storage for the distribution size. Factory methods are provided for any
discrete distribution, and the Poisson and Binomial distributions.

RNG-101: Fixed PMD issues.

This involves a refactor to break up large methods.
Add construction benchmark for generating the seed array.
Added a baseline for JMH consuming new objects.
Removed trailing whitespace.
Javadoc: Use "file name" instead of "filename".
Merge branch 'feature-RNG-101'

RNG-101: Track changes.

Closes #41

RNG-77: Improve NumberFactory to/from byte arrays performance.

Changes the methods to read and write directly from the input / output
arrays avoiding creating an intermediate small array.
RNG-77: Fix checkstyle

Merge pull request #37 from aherbert/improvement-RNG-77

RNG-77: Improve NumberFactory to/from byte arrays performance.
Update construction benchmark to test array seed creation.
Add Integer/Long seed creation time benchmark.
Do not require Int/LongSizes for createInteger/Long seed.
Renamed methods for JMH to avoid failed build on JDK 9

RNG-75: Update ProviderBuilder factory methods.

Allow the RandomSourceInternal to create the seed. This can control the
size of array seeds and provisions for future changes where the seed has
requirements other than just random bits.
RNG-75: Limit use of the synchronized method when creating array seeds.
RNG-75: Return correct type from each enum.
RNG-75: Use SplitMix64.next()
RNG-75: Add coverage tests.

msg: RNG-75: Removed check that create/convert seed returns native type.
Fix line length violation.
Add stress test option to combine bits with a system identity hash code.
RNG-75: Moved NativeSeedType to a new class.
RNG-75: Added @since 1.3 Javadoc tags to new methods/classes.
Add option to combine generator output with ThreadLocalRandom.
Update Help message for the ThreadLocalRandom option
RNG-75: Renamed local and class level constructor variables.
Merge branch 'improvement-RNG-75'

RNG-75: Track changes.

Closes #46
RNG-103: Use KempSmallMeanPoissonSampler in LargeMeanPoissonSampler.

RNG-103: Track changes.

Closes #47

Revert "RNG-75: Use SplitMix64.next()"

This reverts commit aa246979feb8c880c60c972faf7c9ffb9174f4cd.

If the generator is changed in the future to an IntProvider then next() will output an integer and not a long.
Add option to combine primary test generator with a second generator.
Updated second generator javadoc.
RNG-97: Define the JumpableUniformRandomProvider interface.

RNG-97: Implement jump() function in XorShiRo generators.

Assert the pre- and post-jump output sequences.

RNG-97: Move common tests to JumpableProvidersParametricTest.

Add test that the default state in IntProvider and LongProvider is reset
after a jump.

composeStateInternal requires arguments [state, parentState].

The current method uses [parentState, state] but parentState is a zero
byte array so the result is the same. This correction matches the
Javadoc for composeStateInternal.
Merge branch 'feature-RNG-97'
Typo: remove hyphen.

RNG-97: Track changes.

Closes #48
Test generators known to be non-functional with a zero-byte seed.
RNG-98: Added LongJumpableUniformRandomProvider interface.
RNG-98: Implement and test LongJumpableUniformRandomProvider.

RNG-98: Track changes.

Closes #49

RNG-107: Enable checkstyle for the test sources.

- Add space around =
- Remove unnecessary parenthesis
- Remove unused imports
- Fix whitespace around braces
- Suppress certain allowed checks using suppressions file
- Fix indentation
RNG-106: Ensure SeedFactory produces non-zero seed arrays.
RNG-106: Track changes.

RNG-100: Add a GuideTableDiscreteSampler.

This can sample from any distribution defined by an array of
probabilities.
RNG-100: Track changes.

Upgrade parent to 48.

Removed versions superseded by the parent POM.

Downgrade JXR from parent-48 v3.0.0 to 2.5 for multi-module site build.
Downgrade org.apache.felix:maven-bundle-plugin for JDK 7 support.
RNG-104: Add JMH benchmarks for seed creation.
Removed deprecated binary testendianness from .gitignore
Ignore .repository
Exclude SeedFactory from PMD ClassNamingConventions rule.

RNG-99: Add an AliasMethodDiscreteSampler

This can sample from any discrete probability distribution defined by an
array of probabilities.
RNG-99: Track changes.

RNG-108: Update the SeedFactory to improve performance

- Use XorShift1024SPhi
- Use a ReentrantLock for synchronization
- Output arrays using blocks of numbers per synchronisation event
RNG-108: Fixed typo.
RNG-108: Track changes.
Use HTTPS links to commons.apache.org.
Use HTTPS to access Apache resources.
Use HTTPS to access Apache resources.
RNG-102: RandomAssert utility for testing samplers.
RNG-102: Implement the SharedStateSampler interface.
RNG-102: Allow PMD long class for MarsagliaTsangWangDiscreteSampler.
RNG-102: Suppress checkstyle 'rng' hidden field warning for Samplers.
RNG-102: Track changes.

Update SeedFactory use of SecureRandom to non-blocking on Linux systems.

See https://tersesystems.com/blog/2015/12/17/the-right-way-to-use-securerandom/
Add test for PoissonSamplerCache.getMinimumCachedMean().
Fix the site's source repository link.

Ensure the public SamplerBase class is tested.

Although the class is deprecated a public facing API should be verified
to function as expected.
Remove JVM unsupported on Travis.

Run the default Maven goal.

This adds the following goals to the previous config:

- apache-rat:check
- javadoc:javadoc

The build does not require a prior install step so this has been skipped.

After success submit the coverage report.
Ensure rat plugin config matches between build and reporting sections.

Use commons parent defaults for coverage.

These are stricter than the overrides that have been removed:

classRatio 0.96 -> 1.0
instructionRatio 0.8 -> 0.9
methodRatio 0.8 -> 0.95
branchRatio 0.8 -> 0.85
complexityRatio 0.8 -> 0.85
lineRatio 0.85 -> 0.9

Removed jacoco travis profile and use commons-parent profile.

Added a pre jdk-8 profile to change the default goal to ignore JDK 8 plugins.
These cause Travis to fail on the JDK 7 build.

Update test p-value from 0.01 to 0.0001.

Re-runs are not configured for rng-simple. The effect is the same as
configuring 1 re-run as per the rng-sampling module.

RNG-84 : Add members of the PCG suite of generators

Added the LCG and MCG 32 bit output versions of the XSH-RS and XSH-RR
operations, along with the 64 bit RXS-M-XS edition.

msg:
Simplify shared state implementations using NormalizedGaussianSampler.

Throw an UnsupportedOperationException if the NormalizedGaussianSampler
cannot shared state.

Specify trusty to allow use of openjdk7 in the build matrix.

The default xenial build environment does not support openjdk7.

RNG-110: Add SharedStateDiscreteSampler and SharedStateContinuousSampler

These interfaces define functionality for all distribution samplers.

RNG-110: Make distributions samplers implement SharedStateXXXSampler.

XXX is Discrete or Continuous.

All withUniformRandomProvider implementations updated to return an
instance of the appropriate interface.
RNG-110: Return the specialised delegate from withUniformRandomProvider.

RNG-110: PMD rule exceptions to allow Sampler factory constructors.

Samplers can be utility classes without a Utils/Helper suffix.

Samplers can have short method names, e.g. of(...).

RNG-110: Provide factory constructors for unreleased samplers.

These samplers have no requirement to maintain an instance constructor.
The constructor has been made private.

RNG-110: Provide factory constructors for released samplers.

These samplers must maintain an instance constructor for binary
compatibility.
RNG-110: Fix javadoc and formatting.
RNG-110: Track changes.
Remove unused imports.
Remove trailing whitespace.
Checkstyle check to fail on violation.
Add code coverage test for large FactorialLog cache size.

Test the LargeMeanPoissonSampler at small mean.

A small mean is required to hit the case where the sample from the
normal distribution is rejected.

Use constructor for NormalisedGaussianSamplers.

This is a workaround for a JDK 1.6 bug where generic type inference
fails for type variable return constraint.

See: https://bugs.java.com/bugdatabase/view_bug.do?bug_id=6302954
Add edge case for sampler pair rejection.
Fixed javadoc link tags.

Suppress checkstyle failure for this module.

Checkstyle requires loading exception classes mentioned in the @throws
tag to check whether they are RuntimeExceptions. The custom
ApplicationException cannot be loaded and this causes the default build
to fail on the checkstyle:check goal unless the failure is ignored.

RNG-95: Update the DiscreteUniformSampler using faster algorithms.

Algorithms are added for ranges that are a power of 2 and non-power of
2.

Now specifically handles a lower bound of 0.
RNG-95: Track changes.

RNG-90: Use faster algorithm for nextInt(int).

See Lemire (2019): Fast Random Integer Generation in an Interval
https://arxiv.org/abs/1805.10941
RNG-90: Track changes.
RNG-85: Added Middle-Square Weyl Sequence generator.

RNG-85: Added SeedUtils to allow generation of hex permutations.

This is to be used to seed the Middle Square Weyl Sequence generator.

RNG-85: Add Middle Square Weyl Sequence to RandomSource enum.

The generator requires a high quality seed is generated using a custom
seeding routine.

RNG-85: Add MSWS to the tests.

This requires an exclusion for the test of self-seeding functionality.
RNG-85: Add custom nextLong() implementation to MSWS generator.
RNG-85: Allow primitive types to correctly seed the MSWS
RNG-85: Track changes.
Add stress test results for MSWS generator.

RNG-109: Benchmark enumerated probability distributed samplers.

Remove unused import

This allows baselining the speed of the tested RNGs without any sampler

loop.

POM file standardization.

Cf. https://markmail.org/message/obiklp3oeuu7y2fc

msg:
RNG-115: Fix JDKRandom to restore state to a new instance.

Save the state size to the byte array representation. This can be read
by any instance when restoring.
RNG-115: Track changes.

RNG-19: Create a wrapper for JDK Random.

This can wrap a SecureRandom instance to provide access to the
underlying OS source of randomness when on a supported platform.
RNG-19: Track changes.
https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/INFRA/.asf.yaml+features+for+git+repositories

Revert "https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/INFRA/.asf.yaml+features+for+git+repositories"

This reverts commit a506c3dd48346f9d0d106766729700c3b1229b2e.

Not an appropriate location for this file and the features it enables.

Make method explicitly synchronized to match parent class implementation.

Fix suggested by SonarQube.
RNG-114: Add a List shuffle benchmark.

RNG-114: Update ListSampler to detect RandomAccess lists.

RandomAccess lists can be shuffled in-place. Non-RandomAccess lists
should be shuffle as an extracted array and updated using their list
iterator.
RNG-114: Track changes.

JDKRandomBridge: Ignore PMD warning about method level synchronization.

This synchronized method is an override of the super-class method which
is synchronized.
Badge for "SonarQube" analysis.
Create the exponent to Math.pow explicitly as a double.
Extract assignment out of expression.
Extract assignment out of expression.
Extract assignment out of expression.
Comment reversal of parameters

Removed TODO comment.

There is no current requirement for this class to be a separate
component.

Removed commented out sections of pom.xml.

<aggregate> tag from javadoc plugin.

-verbose argument from compiler-plugin.
Updated comment about the examples modules.
Add an assertion to tests without full length seeds.

Comment tests with no assertions.

These tests pass if an exception is not thrown with zero length arrays.
Improved comments for tests with no assertions.

Reinstate ignored tests for all zero seeds.

The test now checks the generator is functional (produces non-zero
output). If true it is tested statistically. If false the generator is
assumed to be non-functional and the test is skipped.

This allows the test to ignore xor-shift based generators that require
some bits in the state pool.
Assert the self-seeded generator output.
MiddleSquareWeylSequence to generate valid output when self-seeded.
RNG-111: Added Jenkins's small fast (JSF) generator.
RNG-111: Added stress test results

msg: RNG-111: Track changes.

Update commons-parent to 49.

Removed javadoc <source> fix as it is present in the parent.
Moved downgrade of felix version to the pre-Java 8 profile.
Renamed SFC generators to DotyHumphreySmallFastCounting.
Renamed JSF generators to JenkinsSmallFast.
Changed user guide sampler examples to use factory constructors
Added JumpableUniformRandomProvider to the user guide.
Added ListSampler to the user guide.
Added SharedStateSampler to the user guide.
Add LongJumpable and Jumpable interfaces to user guide library layout.
Override animal-sniffer.version for pre-Java 8 builds.
Fix RandomSource javadoc stating the correct seed is created if null.
Fix trailing whitespace.
Fixed stress test APT column alignment format.

Updated the user guide performance section.

Removed user guide table for MarsagliaNormalizedGaussianSampler. This
table is redundant given the guide contains a table for all the
normalized Gaussian samplers.

Updated user guide performance benchmarks for next generation. The
section now has a single table with results for next boolean, double,
long, float and int,

Updated the normalized Gaussian sampler section with new results.

Updated the benchmark platform specification.

Sorted tables using the order of RandomSource. This allows each table to
be compared to the Quality section which uses the same order.
Added missing PCG_MCG_XSH_RR_32 stress test results.
Update Javadoc stating that generated seeds are limited to max 128.
RandomSource javadoc: Removed native seed size from all non-array seeds.
Copy updated providers common tests from core  module to simple module.
Added example of how to benchmark named generators using JMH parameters

Updated user guide performance table.

Manually re-ran any score with a high error so that score/error < 0.03.
Updated the table to use the mean of 10 runs not the median.

Checked scores using a correlation of nextFloat vs nextInt and
nextDouble vs nextLong should be close to 1. Manually re-ran outliers to
verify the timing results.

Fixed outlier MSWS. It should be the fastest int generator (results
already stated it is the fastest float generator).

The PCG RR variants are verified outliers (slower then expected) for
nextFloat generation.

Final table:

double vs long  R^2 = 0.9934
float  vs int   R^2 = 0.9831

RNG-117: Update POM to allow test re-runs.

The tests for creating a generator from a random seed may spuriously
fail.
RNG-117: Track changes.

RandomSource.create(RandomSource) can directly call ProviderBuilder.

Added a test of the generator produced for this code execution path.
Reduce RandomSourceInternal method scope where possible.
javadoc: Fix @throw to @throws
Removed the null seed argument to RandomSource.create.

Changed samplers parametric test failure probability.

Only 1 re-run is allowed and the number of samplers is high enough that
spurious failures are realistic for the samplers.

Changed the Continuous samplers failure rate from p=0.0138 to p=0.0016.
This is an effective change of numFailures(n=50, p=0.01) > 2 to
numFailures(n=50, p=0.01) > 3.

Changed the Discrete samplers failure rate from p=0.0000189 to p=0.0016
to match the continuous samplers test. Each test is now assessed at the
p=0.01 level not the p=0.001 level. This is an effective change of
numFailures(n=50, p=0.001) > 2 to numFailures(n=50, p=0.01) > 3.

RNG-119: Add LongJumpable support to XoShiRo generators.

This adds the long jump function to those generators previously
supporting only a jump function.
RNG-119: Track changes.
Report the seed and native byte order to the stress test file.
javadoc: Replace boiler plate text with {@inheritDoc}.

Drop commons-codec dependency and extract the Hex encoding function.

This reduces the shaded jar size by 135K (>25%).
Fix PMD errors in stress test code.
Fix PMD errors in sampling examples code.
Fix PMD errors in quadrature examples code.
Fix PMD errors in JMH examples code.

XoRoShiRo128PlusPlus
XoShiRo256PlusPlus
XoShiRo512PlusPlus
XoRoShiRo1024PlusPlus

msg: RNG-76: Added primitive long constructor to SplitMix64
RNG-76: Track changes.

Updated user guide performance tables.

Added new XoShiRo PlusPlus generators.

Main tables were generated using the mean of 10 runs. Any run where the
error/mean was > 0.02 was repeated.

Correlations:
int  vs float   R^2 = 0.9828
long vs double  R^2 = 0.9933

Normalised Gaussian tables were generated using the mean of 5 runs. Any
run where the error/mean was > 0.02 was repeated.
Added example of how to run a specific sampler benchmark.
Refactored the JMH examples to packages for each component.
RNG-120: Fix security issues in serialization code for Random instances.
RNG-120: Track changes.
Add options to test the upper or lower 32-bits from nextLong().
javadoc: Correct description of beta sampler and algorithmBC.

MersenneTwister: Refactor state filling procedure into sub-methods.

Addresses complexity issue raised by SonarCloud.

LargeMeanPoissonSampler: Added comments of the algorithm steps.

The steps are taken from the reference paper by Devroye.

RNG-121: ChengBetaSampler algorithms delegated to specialised classes.

Allows precomputation of factors including one Math.log() constant used
each loop iteration.
RNG-122: Use XoRoShiRo1024PlusPlus as the default source of randomness.

ChengBetaSampler: Update from reference paper.

Comment algorithm steps.

Change constants to double precision using the reference paper
definitions.

Comment clipping of w to Double.MAX_VALUE.

These changes clarify the algorithm to address the complexity issue
raised by sonar.

Refactor the duplicate code in the XorShiRo generators to the parent.

This implements the common code in the next() generation method in the
abstract parent. Concrete implementations now provide a method to get
the next output value given the current state.

Removed endianness detection and byte reversal.

This is done in the java application. Doing it twice results in
incorrect data.
Increased buffer size to match the buffer size in the java application.
Fix typo in output filename.
Option to list only int/long providers
Option to output 32 or 64-bit from stdin

Updated stress test application for 64-bit test applications.

64-bit support is required for PractRand which can test 64-bit
generators.

Added a custom RNG data output class to write byte data. This handles
endianess conversion when writing thus removing the requirement to do
this in code. It also removes synchronization of the
BufferedOutputStream. BigCrush runs approximately 2 times faster with
the modified application bridge code.

Fix stdout argument example to raw32.

Fix code documentation of 'bridge' command.

Created Hex class for encoding/decoding hex bytes.

Added hex seed option to the output command.
Progress tracker to estimate time remaining.
Added systematic failures report to stress test application.

Allow ignoring partial results files in the results report.

This allows the results to be examined while the test application is
still running.
Timestamp the progress logging and store the ETA.
Added command to delete partial results files.
Added example of how to test using lower bits of a long provider.
Create test tasks before submitting to allow validation of created RNGs.
Fix error in results command APT output format.

Updated BigCrush test results.

These replace the previous results which referred to a byte reversed
32-bit sequence.

Notable changes:

JDK : 74,72,74,73,74 -> 50,51,52,49,51
TWO_CMRES : 4,3,3,5,4 -> 0,1,0,0,0
XO_SHI_RO_128_PLUS : 1,2,2,1,1 -> 0,0,1,0,0

Changes of systematic failures:

JDK                : 70 -> 48
TWO_CMRES          :  3 ->  0
XO_SHI_RO_128_PLUS :  1 ->  0

Unchanged systematic failures:

WELL_* and MT variants systematically fail linear complexity. WELL_512
and 1024 also fail matrix rank.

The other generators have similar results, i.e. no systematic failures.
Detect endianness for raw64 debugging output.

Update stdin2testuO1 to have a true 64 bit reader of stdin.

Drop endianness check.
Find the exit code in the results footer to mark test completion.

Change stress test application process timeout to 60s from 1s.

PractRand may take longer to shutdown when large memory allocation has
occurred.
Estimate time remaining when submitting tasks.
Better time estimate for stress test tasks.
Fix formatting width typo in list command.

APT results format to highlight RNGs with no systematic failures.

Highlight is in bold.

Optionally add systematic failures in brackets.

Updated userguide.

Added examples for:

- RandomSource.isJumpable()
- CombinationSampler

Updated example for CollectionSampler to use Set not List.

Add notes on the speed of nextBoolean.

Highlight RNGs with no systematic failures in bold.

Use binary search upper bound for the time estimate.

This ensures the time cut-off is >50% max run-time.

Read PractRand results.

Report PractRand results using the exponent of the size of output from
the RNG before failure.

Summarise across results using the maximum output size in human readable bytes where a failure occurred,
e.g. TXT output:

RNG          PractRand       ∩
JDK          18,19,19,19,19  512 KiB
WELL_512_A   24,24,24,24,24  16 MiB
ISAAC        -,-,-,-,-
Do not report results if ignorePartialResults is true.

Updated stress test progress reporting to show end of test.

Previously progress was reported when tasks were submitted. This has
been changed to show when tasks are submitted or end. The progress is
only reported at intervals to prevent too many messages.

The end of the final task is always logged.
Results command to summarise PractRand failure length if all failed.
Substitute custom rotl function for Long.rotateLeft.

Removed unreachable code from seeding routine.

The code comment is clear that the two values for seeding are positive
16-bit integers. A test has been added to verify a single bit change in
the seed makes the output different. Thus all 32-bits of the seed are
used to construct two 16-bit integers.
Moved test for a different RNG output to RandomAssert.

Add hex seed option to stress command.

Allows the output command and stress command to stream the same data.
Also allows tests to be repeated.
Add test for round trip of seeds from bytes to chars.
Added patch for PractRand v0.93 to flush stdout after each incremental result.

Updated stress command to allow application threads argument.

This supports smart computation of concurrent tasks for multi-threaded
test applications such as PractRand.
Updated stress test documentation for PractRand.
Update stdin2testu01 raw modes to have a maximum output argument.
Update endianness documentation.

Update stress test documentation.

Added example memory usage figures.

Updated 64-bit generator testing section.
Updated PractRand patch files to fix linux compilation.
Exclude patch files from rat check.
Badge.

Update Long2IntArray to fill the array in reverse.

This addresses a false positive alert for a potential array index out of
bounds exception raised by LGTM.com.
Update PractRand memory usage examples.
Results command to list test application names in encountered order.
Add PractRand results to the userguide.

msg: Updated user guide notes on the Gaussian sampler results.
Changed release howto section on KEYS file.
Change release howto git-wip-us.apache.org to gitbox.apache.org.
Add multi-module update-versions example to release howto.
Added/Updated @since 1.3 javadoc tags to new API.
Release howto to use the -N flag for multi-module download page creation
Add mvn versions:set command to release howto.
Added PractRand to site main (index) page.
Jira report to contain 'Implemented' resolution.

Enable JApiCmp for JDK 1.8+.

Requires moving <commons.bc.version> from the dist-archive module to the
top level pom.
Updated changes and download XML files following 1.3 release.
Updated 1.3 release manager in dist-archive pom.
Updated version from 1.3-SNAPSHOT to 1.4-SNAPSHOT.
Update release notes using the 1.3-release branch.
Update the released verions in the master pom.
Update README.md released version to 1.3.

Ensure consistent formatting across release notes.

Each set of notes has the previous notes appended.

Updated changes.xml so auto-generation of release notes wraps to 100
characters.
Copy release history from 1.3-release branch.
Update release howto following release of 1.3.
Change to the example announce template.
Skip JaCoCo aggregate reports.

Updated the pre-site svn checkout.

Due to the use of modules in sub-directories the existing command did
not exclude the javadocs from checkout. The command has been changed to
process each module directory separately.

Update site checkout to copy from the parent directory if available.

The multi-module setup allows the site checkout done in the parent
directory to be recursively copied by all the child modules. This makes
a site build from a clean checkout avoid repeat svn checkout of the
entire site.

Remove the site-content directories:

mvn clean -Pclean-checkout

Recreate the site-content directories:

mvn pre-site
Only enable japicmp in modules requiring binary compatibility.

Enable japicmp only if on Java 1.8+ using properties.

The use of src/site/resources/profile.japicmp relies on the parent
checking for Java 1.8 in the japicmp profile. This is currently not
done.

Added notes about requirements for the recursive site checkout.

The Maven reactor activates all profiles at start-up. Thus if the parent
is missing the site-content directory all the child modules will also be
configured to check out a copy using svn.

The parent must have a checkout performed first:

mvn -N pre-site && mavn pre-site
Fix update instructions for the website.

Update site menu for the modules.

- Add release 1.3 javadoc link
- Fix relative path for the top right banner image and link

Clarify release notes on where to update the site.xml.

Update <source> example for the sampling index page.

Correct the formatting and switch to using the 'of' factory constructor.
xdoc <source> tag is not allowed inside paragraphs.

Doxia: Remove nested block level elements. This removes
    elements from inside

    elements.

Update developers guidelines.

There is no need to configure core.autocrlf as the repo uses
.gitattributes.

Use https for links if available.

Updated some expired links:

Numerical recipes
Apache CLA
Oracle Code guidelines

Removed reference to RNG wishlist. It is not available on Confluence.

Moved <head> tag of site descriptor.

The tag must be before <body>. However it still does not enable MathJax.
Tests using the <footer> tag are also ignored in the final site so the
tags must be being replaced by other content.
Add PractRand to development howto guide.

Use full URL for the banner.

This allows the project information pages to have a correct link back to
the top level page.
Use "prettyprint" in <source> tag.
Typo (userguide).
Doxia is not rendering <code> tag. Switch to <kbd>.
Update the svn site checkout to use regex for modules.
Update MathJax URL.

Update to 1.4-SNAPSHOT in dist-archive.

Fix command in release howto to update the versions.

Updated to create empty site-content directories for child modules.

A svn checkout of the site is only performed in the parent directory.

Customise jira report.

Removed duplicate configuration from commons-parent.

Jira report for modules to only include those tickets using the
component tag.
Do not perform a full website svn checkout.

Use source class="none" to avoid prettyprint rendering.

If the <source> tag has no class then it will be labelled with the
"prettyprint" class by the new commons-skin release.
Javadoc capitalisation typo.
Changed checkstyle exclusion for pom.properties.

[RNG-124]: Add fixed increment PCG generators.

Adds a single Long argument constructor to:

AbstractPcg6432
PcgXshRr32
PcgXshRs32
PcgRxsMXs64

Adds RandomSource:

PCG_XSH_RR_32_OS
PCG_XSH_RS_32_OS
PCG_RXS_M_XS_64_OS
[RNG-124] Track changes.
Add stress test results for new fixed increment PCG generators.

RNG-174: Improve support for non-zero seeds

Allow specification of a range for array seeds that must be non-zero.

The values for the range are based on the result of
o.a.c.rng.simple.ProvidersCommonParametricTest.testZeroIntArraySeed.

See also the core module for tests using:
- RandomAssert.assertNextIntZeroOutput
- RandomAssert.assertIntArrayConstructorWithSingleBitInPoolIsFunctional

Any generator that fails these tests requires a non-zero seed. In most
cases this was set as the full seed length, or one less for generators
that do not use all the bits of the seed array (WELL_19937_x,
WELL_44497_x).

Notable exceptions:

The KISS generator is reduced to a simple LCG when positions [0, 3) are
all zero. Added a test to demonstrate this. With a zero seed the KISS
LCG passes testZeroIntArraySeed. To avoid a poor generator the seed will
be checked to be non-zero in [0, 3).

The MSWS generator is sensitive to the initial state. Added a test to
show that a zero seed creates zero output. Updating RandomAssert to add
an assertLongArrayConstructorWithSingleBitInPoolIsFunctional test shows
the MSWS fails with single bit seeds. The sub-range has been set to [2,
3) to ensure a non-zero Weyl increment which is the best way to escape a
bad seed. This is a functionally breaking change.

This allows building on JDK 17
Spotbugs excludes for updated spotbugs version
Use the copy constructor

RNG-168: LXM family of random number generators

Add support for generators included in JDK 17:

L32X64Mix
L64X128StarStar
L64X128Mix
L64X256Mix
L64X1024Mix
L128X128Mix
L128X256Mix
L128X1024Mix

Added benchmark for support routines for computing the unsigned long
multiplications in the 128-bit LCG (linear congruential generator).

Added a benchmark for the jump function to allow comparison with the
equivalent base XBG (xor-based generator).

Added a faster carry computation than the method provided in the
reference LXM paper.

msg: RNG-168: Track changes
Set permissions for GH Actions
RNG-177: Add stream methods to the sampler API
RNG-177: Add streaming examples to the user guide
RNG-177: Track changes
Sonar fix: Use @ParameterizedTest
Sonar fix: lambdas to have 1 invocation possible throwing an exception
Remove public test modifier

Do not leak package-private class in public API

Reduces the 'protected' copy method to 'package-private'.

This issue was detected using the revapi maven plugin.
Add revapi plugin for binary compatibility check

Add explicit dependency from simple to the client-api module

The simple module uses interfaces from the client-api that can be after
v1.0. Add an explicit dependency to avoid transitive dependency
resolution creating mismatched modules.

RNG-176: Enhance the UniformRandomProvider interface

Add methods for streams and generation of numbers in a range. The
methods match those implementations in JDK 17 RandomGenerator interface.

Add default implementations of the existing interface methods using
nextLong() as the source of randomness.

RNG-176: Update anonymous implementations of UniformRandomProvider

Only one method is required to implement the interface. This simplifies
creation of implementations for testing edge cases.

For a delegate implementation then additional methods must be added.
This applies to RandomSource.unrestorable.

RNG-176: Remove redundant methods from core module

The methods are now present as default implementations in the client-api
UniformRandomProvider.

This requires JApiCmp is disabled as it does not recognise the change as
compatible. Binary compatibility is checked by revapi which allows this
change.
RNG-176: Update user guide with new UniformRandomProvider methods
RNG-176: Track changes
Javadoc
RNG-178: Add stream support to JumpableUniformRandomProvider
Changes typo
Formatting
Method name typo
Parameter name typo
Simplify returns.
Update GH actions versions

Ignore IntBuffer in animal sniffer

JDK9 breaks compatibility with older versions for IntBuffer.flip() by
returning IntBuffer instead of Buffer.

This ignores this change to allow building on JDK 9+.
Verify the examples in the GH action workflow
Simplify GH build workflow
Fix working directory
Add module javadoc
Run examples on JDK 17
Skip generated files in JMH module
Skip spotbugs in JMH module
Use greater than expression in GH workflow

Use a single build goal

This allows the examples modules to use the dependency artifacts from
the build and not the local repository.
Correct if-else GH action workflow
RNG-179: Add fast loaded dice roller discrete sampler
RNG-179: Track changes

Update README badges

coveralls to codecov
travis to GH actions

Disable Travis CI

Remove Travis profile
Update JMH 1.32 to 1.35

Remove block level element from inside

tags
Remove empty revapi configuration section
Fail build on coverage checks
Increase jacoco method ratio to 1.00
Fail javadoc on warnings
Add missing javadoc checks
Require method javadoc for private scope
Use GitHub Actions setup-java Maven cache property
Migrate workflows from adopt to temurin
Fix some typo and grammar.

Allow javadoc warnings in the JMH module

Enables building on JDK 17
Update README to use the default Maven goal

RNG-180: Add a SplittableUniformRandomProvider interface

Provide default implementations for spliterators to support parallel
streams for the interface stream methods. This includes the parent
UniformRandomProvider interface methods for primitive streams.

Refactor stream tests for UniformRandomProvider to allow the same tests
to be used on SplittableUniformRandomProvider.
Update sub-module README to use the default Maven goal

RNG-181: LXM family to support SplittableUniformRandomProvider

Create generic RandomStreams class that can stream objects created with
a seed and splittable source of randomness. The seed uses the stream
position mixed with random bits to ensure it is unique within the stream
(up to a size limit of 2^60). Use this feature to support splits in the
LXM family.

Add isSplittable method to RandomSource to use to identify supported
interfaces.

Use of the splittable interface by other modules requires an exception
in RevAPI for exposing an external class in the API. This is similar to
exposure of UniformRandomProvider and is allowed. The change is
non-breaking for binary and source compatibility (see revapi
java.class.externalClassExposedInAPI).
RNG-181: Track changes
Add splittable documentation to user guide

Explicit factory method name

Reuse of the method with the annotation @MethodSource(value =
{"testSamplesFrequencies"}) led to a JUnit runtime error on JDK 17 with
commons-parent 54.
Sonar fix: Ensure shift is performed on a long
Sonar fix: Isolate possible source of runtime exception

Update to commons-parent 54

Remove javadoc links. The links configured in CP create redirect
warnings on JDK 17 which fail the build. JDK links are automatically
added by the javadoc plugin based on the target version.

Suppress spotbugs errors from intentional use of floating-point loop
counters.

Disable CycloneDX as config is incorrect for multi-module builds.
spotbugs: Allow floating-point loop control in sampling example
Drop antrun 1.8 for 3.1.0 in commons parent
Drop surefire 3.0.0-M5 for 3.0.0-M7 in commons parent
Drop junit 5.7.2 for 5.9.0 in commons parent

Drop checkstyle 3.1.2 for 3.2.0 in commons parent

Update checkstyle dependency 8.45 for 9.3 in commons parent

Update revapi plugin

maven plugin 0.14.6 -> 0.14.7
java version 0.26.1 -> 0.27.0

Update checkstyle config using latest example

Updated from:
https://github.com/checkstyle/checkstyle/blob/master/src/main/resources/sun_checks.xml
Simplify boolean expression
Correct line number for checkstyle suppression
Remove xdoc processing instruction with reserved name
Add missing @since tags
Add japicmp configuration to reporting section

Rename ObjectFactory to SeededObjectFactory

The name captures the fact that the object is created using a seed
source.
Formatting
Javadoc

Update sampling site page

Remove deprecated API from UnitSphereSampler example.

Use diamond operator.

Use better RNGs for the user examples

Replace Mersenne-Twister (MT) with a more robust xor-based generator
XO_RO_SHI_RO_128_PP

Use better examples for the user guide

Remove use of generators that fail TestU01 BigCrush and/or PractRand.

Use ZigguratSampler.NormalizedGaussian.

Update CollectionSampler example.
Use final

Use randomly chosen high-quality RNG for the sampling tests

RNGs are chosen from those that pass TestU01 BigCrush and PractRand to 4
TiB of output.

Use a fixed seed high-quality RNG for selected sampling tests

Many tests use SPLIT_MIX_64.create(0) to provided a quality generator
with low construction cost. This has been moved to
RandomAssert.seededRNG() where the seed will be fixed for the JVM but
likely to change across JVM instances.

Some tests have been updated to use RandomAssert.createRNG when there is
a stochastic nature to the assertions and re-running would likely pass
the test.

Organisation of imports was performed to consolidate changes across the
test classes.

Update user guide performance tables to include new RNGs
